text: Tulpehocken may refer to: In New Jersey: *Tulpehocken Creek (New Jersey), a tributary of the Wading River In Pennsylvania: *Tulpehocken Creek (Pennsylvania), a tributary of the Schuylkill River *Tulpehocken (SEPTA station), a commuter rail station in the Northwest section of Philadelphia *Tulpehocken Manor Plantation, historic farm in Myerstown *Tulpehocken Station Historic District, Philadelphia *Tulpehocken Township, Pennsylvania, a township in Berks County *Upper Tulpehocken Township, Pennsylvania, a township in Berks County ==See also== *
title: Tulpehocken
